Introduction

DB 
.digital system for data arrangement and storage 
.facilitates efficient management of data
    .enables addition, modification, removal, and access of info

MySQL 
.open-source RDBMS that uses SQL to manage data 
.reliable, fast, and easy to use 
.allows creation, modification, and maintenance of databases 
.provides multiple features:
    .data storage - efficiently store large amounts of data 
    .data retrieval - allows quick and easy access to data 
    .data manipulation - supports ops like inserting, updating, etc 
    .data security - offers robust security features to protect data 
    .scalability - can handle small to large applications with ease 

